<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_bdf39e25-3fba-40b3-908d-31124796b15e" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet climate="Climate zone 8"/></meta><sptc>5.2.3</sptc><title id="_a38944d5-4601-4dfa-a06c-d38e3d4edc62">Openings in masonry veneer</title><archive-num>2019: 3.3.5.11</archive-num><subclause id="_daa2a0ae-0f48-482f-9b26-27fe2a9abf4c" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e1971d1d-9594-4199-b90e-b9499d096c1e">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Except where excluded by (2), openings in masonry veneer must be spanned by steel lintels.</p></subclause><subclause id="_791d7c10-55b6-40ad-b797-772096497b2a" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_a1621527-2523-4e54-971d-3a53373fa70a">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Openings in masonry veneer not more than 500 mm wide need not be provided with a steel lintel provided the opening is adequately supported.</p></subclause></clause>